SEAT BELTS MAINTENANCE

For keeping the seat belts in efficient conditions, carefully observe the following warnings:

always use the seat belt with the strap well stretched and not twisted; make sure that it is free to run without obstructions;

check seat belt operation as follows:

attach the seat belt and pull it hard;

replace the belt after an accident of

a certain severity even if it does not appear to be damaged. Always replace the seat belt if the pretensioners were deployed. Replace the seat belt also when it shows wear or cuts;

prevent the retractors from getting

wet: their correct operation is only guaranteed if water does not get inside.

